rComments: The worst. She is extremely disorganized and very defensive regarding feedback. Not student centred at all...
Literally the worst. So disorganized, clearly does not care about her students. Avoid at all costs. Final exam was an organizational nightmare.

Terrible. Jeanne was unorganized, disrespectful, and uninterested in the success of her students. Lectures were useless and consisted of 30 minutes of references to textbook pages. Expectations were "know everything from entire textbook".  Exam was a nightmare starting over an hour after its expected time due to her organizational skills.

This course was the most frustrating experience I have had at university. Jeanne is extremely disorganized and dismissive/defensive towards feedback. She has no compassion for students. She is VERY knowledgeable but for some reason does not teach during lectures, expecting students to teach themselves everything exclusively from the textbook.
